http://www.thehindu.com/opinion/letters/Beyond-%E2%80%98clicktivism%E2%80%99/article14021364.ece

The Telecom Regulatory Authority of India should explain to the public in simple and easy-to-understand language the steps being taken to counter the arguments of Facebook in the context of net neutrality and how it proposes to make the Internet available to the common man at no extra cost and with no attached riders. In this connection, what is worrisome here is that some India-based Internet Service Providers could join hands with Facebook and fall into a trap laid by the giant social networking site.S. Nallasivan,Tirunelveli